“No matter how dark the night, morning always comes and our journey begins anew“ -LuLu (Final Fantasy X) 🌞🌅🌞 I like to be transparent with the people watching my art. If I’m not honest about my humanity in relation to my art, then what is the point? I make these “meaningful captions” to relate my feelings as the artist to your feelings as the watcher. I want you all to hear me say “Hey! I’m imperfect and I have these feelings, maybe you do too! And if you do, this pipe is for you!”. I want you all to know that I think that whether you are slaving in front of a hot torch for 10 hours in 90 degree weather or sitting in front of a computer with a spread sheet open (which I did for many years before glass) that we may just feel the same things about the grind. Relatability is important to me. We are all humans out here. Sometimes happy, sometimes sad, sometimes super fucking disillusioned and uninspired but fighting through that for reasons other than ourselves. I think ones worth is not held in what you do. It’s held in who your are. To put it simply: “What I want to know is are you kind?” #heady #headyglass #headyart #headylife #headypipes #glass #glasslife #glassart #glasspipes #glasslove #glassappreciation #glassofig #glassporn #glasswork #glassblowing #glassartist #bestofglass #thankyou #dowhatyoulove #supportartists #localart #lawrence #lfk #linework #sherlock #illuminatedglass #katywrightglass
